caption: Right off of the Bergen 2,3 stop so super convenient I had the Bay Ridge crepe super tasty and I added a little garlic thyme dressing for some zing! Friendly staff, clean, lots of healthy choices too. I had a soup on a previous visit and it hit the spot during winter.
Omg!  The BedStuy Vegan Grain Bowl is to die for. The portion is large and I can easily split it into two meals. I love the tahini turmeric dressing.  The guys are also super nice.
My go to place when I head down for a walk and need to energize myself
What can I say, amazing drinks, amazing food on the go. This is my spot I go to when walking downtown Brooklyn

Cute place and cute workers, they are literally the sweetest. Pink drink, berry buzz, and Gold Coast are my fav! I liked their dumbo crepe the last time I came. But my boyfriend ordered the same crepe and it tasted cold. Maybe a technical issue????

This place is busy! I often walk by and see the line out the door. I finally came in today to give it a try. Although small, this place is great. We got the #7 smoothie with açaí berry and apple juice as the liquid and ordered a gluten free crepe with smoked salmon, goat cheese and spinach. It was delicious! The crepe was a little sweet, just like the traditional french crepes. We shared a smoothie and crepe and was the perfect amount for lunch. I’ll be back to try the other delicious looking smoothies and will try to get my next crepe Togo and sit in the park in spring. Can’t wait.

Wonderful!  I passed this place dozens of times before going in, and I have been there almost every other day since!  The crepes are really generous in portion and super fresh.  They make them right there, and the ingredients are fresh...no frozen spinach in these crepes!
Very nice

Stopped in for some ginger shots and they were great! The nice guy behind the counter even took one with us. Loved that they provided free orange slices and water to help us through the struggle. The crepe was also fantastic and filling.
Wasn't the same feeling from the past. Workers seemed stressed out.

Healthiest and most delicious crepes near Park Slope Park in Brooklyn NY. Space is tiny, enough for 4 people seated by the high counter. Besides the tiny spot I was able to give 5 stars for two reasons: great crepes and juices combinations in addition of such a friendly staff.

Alex and Lily gave exceptionally great customer service. Knowledgeable and affable, they created an atmosphere for the store that makes me want to go back soon.
